1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Small brands need a consistent look across
every post. BrandForge turns one Brand Kit
into a coordinated, provenance-tracked
image set, built on Genblaze and Backblaze
B2.

2
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Define a Brand Kit once. One Genblaze
Pipeline generates every variant under a
single SHA-256 manifest, and B2 stores the
assets, the manifest, versioned Brand
Kits, and a Parquet catalog.

3
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:55,000
This is live on Render. Every route but
the health check is behind HTTP Basic auth
that fails closed. Anonymous callers never
see a presigned URL.

4
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:25,000
Here's one campaign: a set of on-brand
images that share the palette and style
from the Brand Kit. Each card carries its
content hash. Provenance, not just pixels.

5
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Replay: I ask for a past campaign by id,
and BrandForge re-queries the Parquet
catalog and re-signs fresh delivery URLs
from B2. The set is reproducible on
demand.

6
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:20,000
On the B2 side: assets under a
hierarchical key strategy, a manifest
beside them, versioned Brand Kits, and one
Parquet index. manifest dot verify re-
hashes every asset. Tamper-evident.

7
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:38,000
It runs on OpenAI's gpt-image-1 today; the
GMI Cloud path and short-video chain are
wired for when credits land. Rate-limited,
security-headered, eighty-three tests,
about ninety-seven percent coverage.

8
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Brand-consistent media, with provenance,
on Genblaze and B2. Repo and live demo are
in the description. Thanks for watching.
